<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="413" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,710,2031]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,854,879]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is distinguished by their body coloration pattern of orange and black; forewing exhibits a transverse amber stripe at midlength and at the apex, beyond of the pterostigma. Male gonocoxites have ten apical spines, subequal in length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="413" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,710,2031]" box="[199,915,962,987]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,372,962,987]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Redescription.</emphasis>
Based on two females and one male, all pinned.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,710,2031]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,270,998,1023]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Head.</emphasis>
Entirely black, mandibles dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[711,778,998,1023]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,208,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. Plega fasciatella: a, forewing; b, hindwing; c, pteropleura; d, head, frontal; e, forefemur, inner and outer surfaces; f, head, thorax and abdomen, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236819/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
Fig. 
<number box="[762,778,998,1023]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
d). Antenna submoniliform, with 
<number box="[1150,1178,999,1023]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="73.0">73</number>
flagellomeres, densely covered with thick black setae (
<figureCitation box="[505,573,1034,1059]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,208,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. Plega fasciatella: a, forewing; b, hindwing; c, pteropleura; d, head, frontal; e, forefemur, inner and outer surfaces; f, head, thorax and abdomen, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236819/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
Fig. 
<number box="[558,573,1034,1059]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
f).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,710,2031]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,1070,1095]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum orange, as long as mesonotum, densely covered with dark brown or orange setae; posteromedial region with a distinct bump; anterior margin medially slightly incised. Meso- and metanotum orange, mesonotum with dark brown setae; metanotum with small light brown or orange setae (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1411,1142,1167]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,208,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. Plega fasciatella: a, forewing; b, hindwing; c, pteropleura; d, head, frontal; e, forefemur, inner and outer surfaces; f, head, thorax and abdomen, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236819/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
Fig. 
<number box="[1396,1411,1142,1167]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
f). Pteropleura orange (
<figureCitation box="[378,447,1178,1203]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,208,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. Plega fasciatella: a, forewing; b, hindwing; c, pteropleura; d, head, frontal; e, forefemur, inner and outer surfaces; f, head, thorax and abdomen, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236819/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
Fig. 
<number box="[431,447,1179,1203]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
c).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,710,2031]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1214,1239]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Legs.</emphasis>
Foreleg with coxa, trochanter and femur orange (
<figureCitation box="[858,932,1214,1239]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,208,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. Plega fasciatella: a, forewing; b, hindwing; c, pteropleura; d, head, frontal; e, forefemur, inner and outer surfaces; f, head, thorax and abdomen, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236819/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
Fig. 
<number box="[916,932,1215,1239]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
e). Trochanter subtriangular with dentiform process on the inner surface. Base of tibia orange, remainder black. First tarsomere amber, other with mixture of orange and black; tarsal claws amber. Mid- and hindleg with coxa, femur and 
<number box="[1059,1069,1287,1311]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1080,1094,1287,1311]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="3.0">3</number>
of tibia orange, remainder of tibial surface and tarsomeres black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,710,2031]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,281,1358,1383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Wings.</emphasis>
Forewing length 9.9‒ 
<quantity box="[556,643,1359,1383]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
; membrane orange translucent, at midlength with a broad amber transverse stripe; vention orange or brown; apex, beyond to pterostigma amber in color (
<figureCitation box="[1146,1215,1394,1419]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,208,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. Plega fasciatella: a, forewing; b, hindwing; c, pteropleura; d, head, frontal; e, forefemur, inner and outer surfaces; f, head, thorax and abdomen, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236819/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
Fig. 
<number box="[1199,1215,1395,1419]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Costal field with 
<number box="[151,220,1430,1455]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="13.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="11.0">11‒15</number>
crossveins; subcostal area with one crossvein at the level of Rs stem. Pterostigma orange, consisting of eigth crossveins. Three veins arising from each anterior radial cell; Rs 
<number box="[890,932,1466,1491]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3‒5</number>
gradate crossveins. Hindwing length 7.3‒ 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
; membrane pale orange, apical area of subcostal field and wing apex, amber. Pterostigma basally dark brown, apically orange (
<figureCitation box="[343,414,1538,1563]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,208,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. Plega fasciatella: a, forewing; b, hindwing; c, pteropleura; d, head, frontal; e, forefemur, inner and outer surfaces; f, head, thorax and abdomen, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236819/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
Fig. 
<number box="[398,414,1538,1563]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Costal field with seven crossveins; three or four veins arising from 
<number box="[1232,1241,1539,1563]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="1.0">1</number>
RA cell and two from 
<number box="[212,226,1575,1599]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="2.0">2</number>
RA; Rs with 
<number box="[373,415,1575,1599]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="1.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="0.0">0‒3</number>
gradate crossveins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,710,2031]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,1610,1635]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Abdominal segments I‒V orange. Segments VI‒IX progressively changing from brown to black. Ectoproct black, covered with long and thick setae (
<figureCitation box="[730,797,1646,1671]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,208,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. Plega fasciatella: a, forewing; b, hindwing; c, pteropleura; d, head, frontal; e, forefemur, inner and outer surfaces; f, head, thorax and abdomen, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236819/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
Fig. 
<number box="[782,797,1646,1671]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
f). Female gonocoxites black or very dark brown, arched, as long as the last four abdominal segments. Sternite VIII dark brown, with prominent dark brown or black setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,710,2031]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,378,1718,1743]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Tergite IX dark brown, except for a depigmented region laterally in the posterior half, entire surface covered with long and thick black setae. Ectoproct in lateral view elongated, elliptical, densely covered with spiniform black setae arising from protuberant bases (
<figureCitation box="[822,902,1790,1815]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1133,1155]" captionTargetBox="[162,1435,206,1111]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1435,193,1112]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. Plega fasciatella: a, male genitalia, ventral; b, male genitalia, lateral; c, apex of gonocoxite, lateral. Scale bars, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236820/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
Figs. 
<number box="[887,902,1790,1815]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Sternite VIII covered with long black setae. Sternite IX subpentagonal, posterolaterally with two pronounced lobes, posteriomedially rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1409,1826,1851]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1133,1155]" captionTargetBox="[162,1435,206,1111]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1435,193,1112]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. Plega fasciatella: a, male genitalia, ventral; b, male genitalia, lateral; c, apex of gonocoxite, lateral. Scale bars, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236820/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
Fig. 
<number box="[1394,1409,1826,1851]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Pseudopenis long, forming a turn at the level of gonocoxite base, apex protruding from abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1406,1862,1887]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1133,1155]" captionTargetBox="[162,1435,206,1111]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1435,193,1112]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. Plega fasciatella: a, male genitalia, ventral; b, male genitalia, lateral; c, apex of gonocoxite, lateral. Scale bars, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236820/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1406,1862,1887]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Gonocoxites cylindrical, elongated, with apex leaving from abdomen; in ventral view curved near to its midlength; ten apical spines subequal in length (
<figureCitation box="[648,716,1934,1959]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1133,1155]" captionTargetBox="[162,1435,206,1111]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1435,193,1112]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. Plega fasciatella: a, male genitalia, ventral; b, male genitalia, lateral; c, apex of gonocoxite, lateral. Scale bars, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236820/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
Fig. 
<number box="[701,716,1934,1959]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
c).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="415" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,710,2031]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1970,1995]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[654,765,1970,1995]" name="Colombia" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Colombia</collectingCountry>
for the first time. It is distributed in Bolívar, Magdalena and Santander (
<figureCitation box="[278,362,2006,2031]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,196,1730]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[151,1435,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 25. Distribution of mantispids in Colombia. 1, Plega and Anchieta species; 2, Trichoscelia species; 3, Buyda species; 4, Climaciella species. Elevation in meters." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236840/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
Fig. 
<number box="[331,362,2006,2031]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Its altitudinal distribution range is between 
<number box="[869,897,2007,2031]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" value="10.0">10</number>
and 
<specimenCount box="[951,1029,2006,2031]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" type="generic">
<quantity box="[951,1025,2006,2031]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" unit="m" value="150.0">150 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236819/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" targetBox="[156,1436,208,1887]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1909,1962]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
